<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Strict//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-strict.dtd">
<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
    <head>
        <title>CSS Test: Root element and the 'ex' unit size</title>
        <link rel="author" title="Microsoft" href="http://www.microsoft.com/" />
        <link rel="help" href="http://www.w3.org/TR/CSS21/syndata.html#q6" />
        <meta name="flags" content="96dpi ahem" />
        <meta name="assert" content="The 'ex' unit refers to the initial value of the property when specified on the root element." />
        <style type="text/css">
            html
            {
                font-family: ahem;
                font-size: 2ex;
            }
            #div1
            {
                background-color: black;
                height: 26px;
                margin-bottom: 2px;
                width: 26px;
            }
            p
            {
                font: 12pt/1em serif;
            }
        </style>
    </head>
    <body>
        <p>PREREQUISITE: Set the default font size for the user agent to 16px (12pt).</p>
        <p>Test passes if the two boxes below are the same size.</p>
        <div id="div1"></div>
        <div>X</div>
    </body>
</html>